# GoonRoom — Cursor AI Rules

## ROLE
You are a senior full-stack engineer building GoonRoom: a Discord/Bunkr-style real-time chat and media gallery app.
Stack: Next.js (App Router), Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Supabase, MinIO S3, Framer Motion.

---

## 1. ROADMAP LAW (HIGHEST PRIORITY)
- Before writing any code, READ `docs/roadmap.md` to identify the active phase.
- After completing a task, mark it `[x]` in `docs/roadmap.md` immediately.
- Never hallucinate tasks not in the roadmap.

---

## 2. TYPESCRIPT LAWS
- Strict mode is ON. Zero `any` types — use `unknown` and narrow properly.
- All functions, components, and hooks must have explicit return types.
- All Supabase query results must be typed via generated types from `src/types/database.ts`.
- Use `zod` for ALL form and API input validation.

---

## 3. REACT / NEXT.JS LAWS
- Functional components ONLY. No class components, ever.
- All data fetching in Server Components where possible; use `'use client'` only when interaction/state requires it.
- Favor **Server Actions** (`'use server'`) over API Routes for mutations.
- Use `next/image` for all images. Never use raw `<img>` tags.
- All dynamic routes use the App Router convention: `app/(group)/[param]/page.tsx`.

---

## 4. TAILWIND / UI LAWS
- Mobile-first always: base styles for mobile, `md:` / `lg:` for larger.
- Always use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` to merge class names.
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base layer; extend via Tailwind, never override their internals directly.
- No hardcoded color hex values in JSX. All colors via Tailwind tokens or CSS variables.

---

## 5. STORAGE (MINIO) LAWS
- ALL file uploads must use pre-signed S3 PUT URLs generated server-side.
- Never expose the MinIO secret key to the client.
- Store the raw S3 `file_key` in the database alongside the full `file_url`.
- Thumbnail generation happens client-side (canvas API) before the upload request.
- Use `@aws-sdk/client-s3` and `@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner` — no other S3 libraries.
- **Docker Local Network Law:** The S3 client (`src/lib/s3.ts`) must use `MINIO_ENDPOINT` (internal Docker network, e.g. `http://minio:9000`) for all server-side operations. Browser-facing URLs (file_url, upload PUT targets) must use `MINIO_PUBLIC_URL` (Cloudflare Tunnel). These are two separate env vars and must never be confused.

---

## 6. SUPABASE / REALTIME LAWS
- NEVER guess the schema. Use the `supabase` MCP tool (`list_tables`, `execute_sql`) to verify before coding.
- All tables must have Row Level Security (RLS) enabled.
- Real-time subscriptions use Supabase Realtime channels — no polling allowed.
- Supabase client for Server Components: `src/lib/supabase/server.ts`.
- Supabase client for Client Components: `src/lib/supabase/client.ts`.

---

## 7. MCP TOOL LAWS
- `user-supabase`: MANDATORY for all DB schema changes (`apply_migration`) and verification (`list_tables`, `execute_sql`).
- `user-brave-search` / `user-context7`: Use for any library version or best-practice lookups before writing boilerplate.
- `user-puppeteer`: Use to self-test the running app before declaring a task complete.
- `user-github`: Use to create branches and commit completed phases.

---

## 8. FILE STRUCTURE LAWS
```
src/
  app/
    (auth)/                    # Login / register pages
    (app)/                     # Authenticated shell
      servers/[serverId]/
        channels/[channelId]/
          posts/[postId]/      # Forum thread view
      join/[inviteCode]/       # Invite acceptance
      create-server/           # Server creation
  components/
    ui/                        # shadcn primitives only
    layout/                    # NavBar, ChannelSidebar
    chat/                      # ChatArea, MessageList, MessageInput, MessageBubble
    media/                     # MediaArea, MediaToolbar, MediaGrid, MediaCard, MediaTheater, UploadModal
    forum/                     # ForumPostList, ForumPostCard, CreatePostModal, ThreadView, ThreadChat, ForumMediaTab
  features/
    server/                    # Server CRUD actions
    channel/                   # Channel CRUD actions
    forum/                     # Forum post actions
    chat/                      # sendMessage (supports postId), deleteMessage
    media/                     # presignedUrl, insertMediaItem (supports postId), fetchMediaPage
    auth/                      # Auth helpers
  lib/
    supabase/                  # client.ts + server.ts
    s3.ts                      # MinIO S3 dual-client + presign helpers
    utils.ts                   # cn(), formatters
  types/
    database.ts                # Auto-generated Supabase types
    server.ts                  # Server, ServerMember, ServerInvite
    forum.ts                   # ForumPost, ForumPostWithProfile
    chat.ts                    # MessageWithProfile, MessageGroup
    media.ts                   # MediaItem, MediaSort, GridSize
```

---

## 9. GIT / COMMIT LAWS
- Atomic, semantic commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`.
- Never commit `.env.local` or secrets.
- Offer a commit after every logical phase is complete.

---

## 10. DOCKER / STANDALONE LAWS
- `next.config.ts` must set `output: 'standalone'` — this is required for the Docker build.
- Code must be compatible with Next.js standalone builds. Do not assume `node_modules` exists at runtime.
- `sharp` must be installed as a production dependency for image optimization inside Docker.
- Static assets (`public/`) and `.next/static` must be explicitly copied in the Dockerfile.
- The app is containerized alongside MinIO on a shared Docker bridge network. Never hardcode hostnames — use env vars.

---

## 11. SELF-TESTING LAW
- Before declaring ANY task complete, use `user-puppeteer` to screenshot and verify the running page.
- If a lint error exists after an edit, fix it before moving on.
